},"displayName":"Haohui Mai","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"This is exactly the situation that we want to avoid -- {{HttpServer}} is a private API and it should not support any downstream uses.\n\nThe only downstream user of this class is HBase. Once HBASE-10336 is landed, you should be clear to upgrade.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wheat9","name":"wheat9","key":"wheat9","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Haohui Mai","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2014-01-22T19:39:16.263+0000","updated":"2014-01-22T19:39:16.263+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12690351/comment/13879088","id":"13879088","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=apurtell","name":"apurtell","key":"apurtell","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553"},"displayName":"Andrew Purtell","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"My read of HBASE-10336 is the change there will be committed to HBase trunk, but not to the 0.96 and 0.98 release branches. For those releases, we will need to add a disclaimer they will not work with Hadoop 2.X where X is wherever the backwards compatibility is broken on the Hadoop 2.x release line. ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=apurtell","name":"apurtell","key":"apurtell","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553"},"displayName":"Andrew Purtell","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2014-01-22T19:41:16.440+0000","updated":"2014-01-22T19:41:16.440+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12690351/comment/13879141","id":"13879141","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=apurtell","name":"apurtell","key":"apurtell","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553"},"displayName":"Andrew Purtell","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"bq. This is exactly the situation that we want to avoid â€“ HttpServer is a private API and it should not support any downstream uses.\n\nI went and reviewed the code in question, and I don't understand this statement. This is the interface annotation for HttpServer on HEAD of Hadoop common branch-2:\n{noformat}\n@InterfaceAudience.LimitedPrivate({\"HDFS\", \"MapReduce\", \"HBase\"})\n@InterfaceStability.Evolving\npublic class HttpServer implements FilterContainer {\n{noformat}","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=apurtell","name":"apurtell","key":"apurtell","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=apurtell&avatarId=20553"},"displayName":"Andrew Purtell","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2014-01-22T20:23:55.820+0000","updated":"2014-01-22T20:23:55.820+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12690351/comment/13879165","id":"13879165","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=stack","name":"stack","key":"stack","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"stack","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"[~wheat9] \"...HttpServer is a private API and it should not support any downstream uses.\"\n\nGo easy.  The above is all well and good as some sort of general statement only there is the caveat that [~apurtell] quotes you above (and which was quoted to you a few days ago over in HADOOP-10232).\n\nI believe the hope was that those listed in the LimitedPrivate set would get notice if the class was to change radically.  Notice noted.  We are moving to get off this Interface now  -- a patch will go in in the next few days and we'll soon enough have a release out with the patch in it -- but please do not remove these methods just yet and make it so releases we have in the field now fail when our users would like to go to apache 2.5/2.6, etc.  Thanks.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=stack","name":"stack","key":"stack","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"stack","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2014-01-22T20:50:58.111+0000","updated":"2014-01-22T20:50:58.111+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12690351/comment/13879248","id":"13879248","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sureshms","name":"sureshms","key":"sureshms","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10450","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10450","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10450","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10450"},"displayName":"Suresh Srinivas","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"bq. HttpServer is a private API and it should not support any downstream uses.\n[~wheat9], given that this class is marked as LimitedPrivate this class cannot be removed or made private. ,The interface is marked as evolving, so incompatible changes should be allowed. However, I suggest just making a copy of this HttpServer (HttpServer2?) for internal use in HDFS and MapReduce, with cleaner code and leave HttpServer class alone. At some point in time when HBase folks are ready, they can copy this to their project and we can delete this from Hadoop, possibly in 3.0.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sureshms","name":"sureshms","key":"sureshms","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10450","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10450","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10450","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10450"},"displayName":"Suresh Srinivas","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2014-01-22T22:02:50.822+0000","updated":"2014-01-22T22:02:50.822+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12690351/comment/13879268","id":"13879268","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jxiang","name":"jxiang","key":"jxiang","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jimmy Xiang","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"+1 to make a copy of this HttpServer and bring the original HttpServer back.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jxiang","name":"jxiang","key":"jxiang","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jimmy Xiang","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2014-01-22T22:15:24.945+0000","updated":"2014-01-22T22:15:24.945+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12690351/comment/13879292","id":"13879292","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jxiang","name":"jxiang","key":